CatDescriptText: Dr. T. J. King served Ebenezer Baptist Church from 1926 to 1949.  He was a member of Board of Control Pennsylvania State Prison, Tuberculosis League, Society of Catholics, Jews, and Protestants, Trustee of the Virginia Theological Seminary and College, National Baptist Foreign Mission Board, and Corresponding Secretary of the New England Baptist Convention. He died Wednesday, February 23, 1949, in New York.
TitMainTitle: Crowd of women and men gathered outside of Ebenezer Baptist Church for funeral of Dr. Thomas Jefferson King, eighth pastor of Ebenezer Baptist Church, with hearse from West Funeral Home in foreground
